The paper deals with randomized query complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also introduces a new complexity measure called conflict complexity, which may be of interest to researchers in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the composition of relations and partial Boolean functions, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and cryptography (cs.CR).
